<div class="flex flex-col font-light mx-8">
    <div class="flex flex-row gap-8 py-[8rem]">
        <img src="Rules_Icon.png" alt="Rules Icon" class="h-[96px]" />
        <div class="flex flex-col">
            <p class="text-5xl">Offical Ruleset of</p>
            <p class="text-5xl font-bold">CHALLENGE CUP</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-8 text-2xl">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold my-4">General Rules</h1>
            <p>- <b class="font-bold">All players are to play to the best of their abilities at all times during the tournament. “Throwing” a match and/or map is grounds for a match forfeit and/or disqualification.</b></p>
            <p>- All players are required to submit scores on <b class="font-bold">all of the Qualifier maps</b> to participate in the tournament.</p>
            <p>- All players are required to be <b class="font-bold">able to stream on Twitch and/or an RTMP server at a minimum of 480p 30fps.</b></p>
            <p>- Players are asked to <b class="font-bold">refrain from using chat mods, streams must be in first person without an avatar.</b></p>
            <p>- Overlays <b class="font-bold">are allowed</b> but they <b class="font-bold">must not obstruct the stream too much</b> and must be <b class="font-bold">in good taste.</b></p>
            <p>- All team captains must be <b class="font-bold">able to be contacted via Discord and be available.</b></p>
            <p>- <b class="font-bold">Coordinators</b> and <b class="font-bold">Team Captains</b> are <b class="font-bold">expected to read the ruleset</b> to facilitate match flow.</p>
            <p>- Coordinators are <b class="font-bold">required to report all issues and/or discrepancies to organizers.</b></p>
            <p>- <b class="font-bold">All Tournament Staff members, organizers and players must be shown respect at all times. Inappropriate behavior may result in a forfeited match and/or disqualification.</b></p>
            <p>- Situations <b class="font-bold">not included in the rules</b> will be <b class="font-bold">handled by your Match Coordinator, Tournament Staff and Organizers.</b></p>
            <p>- Any decision <b class="font-bold">made by an Organizer is final and will not be overturned.</b></p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold my-4">Mod & Plugin Rules</h1>
            <p>- Custom notes <b class="font-bold">are allowed.</b></p>
            <p>- All mods <b class="font-bold">besides the blacklisted ones are allowed.</b></p>
        <h2 class="font-bold mt-2">Blacklisted:</h2>
            <p>- Intro/Outro Skip</p>
            <p>- Song Chart Visualizer</p>
            <p>- Note Slice Visualizer</p>
            <p>- All Chat mods</p>
            <p>- Old Notes</p>
            <p>- Any/all mods and plugins that affect score.</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold my-4">Tournament Format</h1>
            <p>- 2v2, teams of 3 players.</p>
            <p>- Double Elimination</p>
            <p>- All matches take place over <b class="font-bold">one weekend.</b></p>
            <p>- Picks and bans will determine maps played during matches.</p>
            <p>- No Fail enabled for all players.</p>
            <p>- Match times will be assigned on <b class="font-bold">June 20th.</b> If you have any questions, please contact an organizer <b class="font-bold">before June 25th</b>.</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold my-4">Match Rules</h1>
            <p>- Team captains will <b class="font-bold">communicate all decisions clearly and directly to the match coordinator.</b></p>
            <p>- The tiebreaker is <b class="font-bold">predetermined.</b></p>
            <p>- Scores are determined by <b class="font-bold">combined misses.</b> In the case of a <b class="font-bold">tie, they are determined by score.</b></p>
            <p>- <b class="font-bold">Each team</b> is allowed a <b class="font-bold">warmup map of a limited time of 3 minutes.</b> Each team <b class="font-bold">may opt out</b> of playing the warmup map. All warmup maps <b class="font-bold">must be sent to the coordinator by the team captain and respect Twitch’s Terms of Services.</b></p>
            <p>- There will be a max <b class="font-bold">3 minute break allowed following each map,</b> replays count as a separate map.</p>
            <p>- Team icons must be <b class="font-bold">tasteful.</b></p>
            <p>- Players <b class="font-bold">may be subbed out between maps, including replays.</b></p>
            <p>- If a player <b class="font-bold">disconnects for any reason</b> during the match, they will <b class="font-bold">have a limit of 10 minutes to reconnect.</b> The team will be <b class="font-bold">forced to play without said player if they cannot reconnect in time.</b> A team with <b class="font-bold">less than 2 players forfeits the match.</b></p>
            <p>- Teams have a <b class="font-bold">10 minute grace period</b> to be present and have a <b class="font-bold">minimum of 2 players ready to play the match.</b> A team that isn’t able to play within the grace period will <b class="font-bold">forfeit the match.</b></p>
            <p>- Each team is <b class="font-bold">allowed one replay per match at the Captain’s discretion.</b> A replay cannot be called on a map that has already been replayed. <b class="font-bold">All replay calls are final and may not be taken back.</b></p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold my-4">Cheesing Rules</h1>
            <p>Most forms of "cheesing" are <b class="font-bold">not allowed</b> in this tournament.</p>
            <p>"Cheesing" on maps marked as "Shitpost" on the Map Pools tab of the Public Sheet <b class="font-bold">is allowed</b> in this tournament.</p>
            <p>The most common forms of "cheesing" are listed below. Being caught "cheesing" on a map that is not shitpost during this tournament <b class="font-bold">may result in a warning and/or a map loss.</b></p>
            <p><b class="font-bold">- NJS Cheesing</b></p>
            <p><b class="font-bold">- Hilt Cheesing</b></p>
            <p><b class="font-bold">- Windshield Wiping</b></p>
            <p><b class="font-bold">- Any other form of cheesing not listed below</b></p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold my-4">Picks and Bans</h1>
            <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold my-4">Coinflip / Roll</h1>
            <p>A roll will <b class="font-bold">determine Team 1 and Team 2.</b> Each Team Captain will use the <b class="font-bold">roll d100 command</b> and the highest score will get to <b class="font-bold">decide which Team they pick to be.</b></p>
            <div class="flex flex-row gap-4 py-[1rem] items-center justify-center">
                <img src="Picks & Bans.png" alt="Picks and Bans Graphic" class="h-[1000px]" />
            </div>
        </div>
</div>